[
    "When discussing the \"fastest\" birds, it is critical to distinguish between **diving speed** (a gravity-assisted \"stoop\" used by raptors to strike prey) and **level flight speed** (sustained flight under the bird's own power).\n\nThe table below ranks birds by their **maximum recorded airspeed**, which almost exclusively favors those capable of high-velocity dives[1](https://www.animalspot.net/fastest-birds), [2](https://www.birdwatchingdaily.com/beginners/birding-faq/the-fastest-birds-in-the-world/).\n\n### Fastest Birds by Maximum Airspeed\n\n| Rank | Common Name | Max Airspeed | Flight Type |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| 1 | **Peregrine Falcon** | ~389 km/h (242 mph)[3](https://www.worldatlas.com/animals/the-fastest-birds-in-the-world.html), [4](https://www.worldatlas.com/animals/the-fastest-birds-in-the-world.html) | Diving (Stoop)[5](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_birds_by_flight_speed), [6](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_birds_by_flight_speed) |\n| 2 | **Golden Eagle** | ~322 km/h (200 mph)[3](https://www.worldatlas.com/animals/the-fastest-birds-in-the-world.html), [6](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_birds_by_flight_speed) | Diving[7](https://www.discoverwildlife.com/animal-facts/birds/fastest-birds-world), [6](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_birds_by_flight_speed) |\n| 3 | **Saker Falcon** | ~320 km/h (200 mph)[3](https://www.worldatlas.com/animals/the-fastest-birds-in-the-world.html), [6](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_birds_by_flight_speed) | Diving[6](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_birds_by_flight_speed) |\n| 4 | **Gyrfalcon** | ~209 km/h (130 mph)[3](https://www.worldatlas.com/animals/the-fastest-birds-in-the-world.html), [6](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_birds_by_flight_speed) | Diving[6](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_birds_by_flight_speed) |\n| 5 | **White-throated Needletail** | ~170 km/h (105 mph)[3](https://www.worldatlas.com/animals/the-fastest-birds-in-the-world.html), [8](https:/